page.title: 13BIRDLIFE (CONTINUED)
page.content: COAL TIT(B),GREAT TIT(B),BLUE TIT(B), MARSH TIT(B),WILLOW TIT(B),NUTHATCH (B),TREECREEPER(B),CORN BUNTING, YELLOW BUNTING(B),REED BUNTING(B), SNOW BUNTING,BRAMBLING,CHAFFINCH(B), GOLDFINCH(B),GREENFINCH(B),BULLFINCH (B),REDPOLL(B),LINNET(B),TREESPARROW (B),HOUSESPARROW(B),STARLING(B),JAY(B) MAGPIE(B),ROOK(B),CARRION CROW(B), JACKDAW(B). IN ADDITION ,MANY MIGRANT SPECIES PASS ANNUALLY THROUGH THE D-BLOCK,AS WELL AS A SPRINKLING OF RARER VAGRANTS SUCH AS OSPREY,HOOPOE AND RICHARD'S PIPIT. GIVEN THE PROXIMITY OF THE BROADS, RIVERS AND BREYDON WATER,A SKILLED OBSERVER COULD PROBABLY SEE OVER 300 DIFFERENT SPECIES IN A SINGLE YEAR.
